    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "activityType": "Discretization convergence study",
    "name": "Mesh independence study for centrifugal pump CFD domain",
    "description": "A systematic mesh independence study was performed across three grid refinement levels (coarse: 1.2M cells, medium: 4.8M cells, fine: 12.1M cells) for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. The Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was computed for the primary quantity of interest (hemolysis index) at the nominal operating point (6 L/min, 3500 RPM). GCI values below 2% were achieved between the medium and fine grids, confirming discretization error is within acceptable bounds for MRL 2. The medium mesh was selected for all production simulations."
  },
